cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.GR, cs.VIS, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on defining new tasks for graph visualization and evaluating visualization techniques. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper mentions social networks as an application field for graph visualization. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.VIS (Visualization and Computer Graphics) are relevant categories as the paper discusses visualization techniques and proposes a new taxonomy for graph visualization tasks. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions biology and software engineering as application fields for graph visualization, which may involve natural language processing.
